Contact: Matt Alvarado and Karen Cady-Pereira (aer_lnfl@aer.com)
FIRST COMPILE AN LNFL EXECUTABLE FOR YOUR SPECIFIC PLATFORM AND COMPILER:

* See README.build_instructions in parent directory

----------------------------------------------------------------------- 

THEN COME BACK TO THE EXAMPLES DIRECTORY AND RUN THE EXECUTABLE WITH THE FILES PROVIDED

    (i.e. in the examples directory modify and execute script "run_lnfl")

   1) Input Files:
                                                                               
      TAPE1      LINE PARAMETER ASCII INPUT FILE IN HITRAN FORMAT    

     co2_co2_brd_param -> CO2 self broadening parameters

     co2_h2o_brd_param -> CO2 transitions broadened by H2O

     o2_h2o_brd_param  -> O2 transitions broadened by H2O

     wv_co2_brd_param  -> H2O transitions broadened by CO2

     spd_dep_param     -> Speed-dependent Voigt parameters        

      TAPE5      LNFL INPUT FILE                                            
                                                                               

   2) Output Files:


      TAPE3      UNFORMATTED BINARY LINE FILE FOR LBLRTM                
                                     
      TAPE6      LNFL LOG FILE CONTAINING INFORMATION ABOUT THE RUN   
                                                                               
      TAPE7      TAPE3 in ASCII format                   
                                                                               
-----------------------------------------------------------------------    

Note:

1) All LNFL computations must be performed in single precision.

2) The mw example generates a TAPE3 file from 0-30 cm-1
   for the first 7 HITRAN molecules
    
3) The program is very flexible so please refer to instructions 
   provided with the code to generate specific TAPE3 



